        <span class="section-label">The Story</span>
        <h2>Built from the<br>Ground Up</h2>
        <p>StageHaus Productions is owned and operated by Shelby Williams. There's no team, no partners, no staff roster — just one person with 10 years of hands-on production experience who decided it was time to do this properly.</p>
        <p>Over the past decade, I've produced small to mid-sized shows primarily in Tulsa, Oklahoma, with a handful of productions in Dallas — including a show at Whiskey Garden. I've worked directly with artists, booked shows, coordinated vendors, managed logistics from load-in to settlement, and handled the hundred moving pieces that make a show actually happen the way it's supposed to.</p>
        <p>I've booked artists including Dr. Jr and have built real working relationships in the Tulsa music community — including a close personal connection with Flint Wick. I know what artists need on show day because I've been in those conversations at soundcheck, in the green room, and at the merch table when things don't go to plan.</p>
        <p>StageHaus is the structure I built around that experience. Boutique by choice, hands-on by design.</p>

